8ï¸âƒ£ Real-world analogy

Hashing â†’ fingerprint (can verify, cannot reconstruct)

Encryption â†’ locked box (can unlock with key)

9ï¸âƒ£ Final takeaway

Use hashing when you only need to verify

Use encryption when you need to retrieve

Passwords â†’ always hashed

Sensitive data â†’ encrypted